caption: For starters this place has the best cheese sauce I've ever encountered.The chips&cheese/nachos are beyond compare.Put that sauce on a horseshoe and it becomes sublime. The Alamo is a decent place for drinks and bar style food. I was there for the 217 Burger Week entrant. It was good. Staff is nice, place looks clean, attracts a fairly mellow crowd and it's a fairly convenient location. Only thing I didn't care for was the live music and that we were literally sat at the table closest to stage and it was impossible to talk to my companions. The music wasn't bad just unexpected which was a bit of a bummer for us. Would go back but would definitely check their live music roster just to be safe.

Alamo is thee anchor when it comes to finding a place to have fun in the Downtown area.  As bars have come and gone to Downtown, it's only fitting the Alamo still stands!) Born and raised in Springfield IL, the owner understands it's nice to have an establishment for no-nonsense good drinks and drink specials that you can look forward too. The Alamo’s uniqueness is it’s large beer garden which is unmatched in the downtown Old State Capitol area. You will find patrons that range from Governors, Mayors to your local part-time server and starving-artist and demographics everywhere in between.  Alamo is a spacious fun unstuffy place to grab a beer and enjoy your fave tunes on the jukebox... Yep, when they don't have any live entertainment of blues, jazz or other genres, you can still find some good tunes on their wall :)
